        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Match the male Lebros Apkallu up to the female Lebros Apkallu. You only need to match up one pair to win, but for every pair less than 8 you will recieve reduced points.\n1. The apkallus in this assault speak in morse code. And you thought they were annoying in Apkallu Seizure!\n      - Squee = dot, Quark = dash.\n2. To match up apkallus you will have to take a male from the west to females in the east.\n3. The male apkallus will follow you a little faster than walking speed.\n4. If you get too far ahead of the male apkallus they will stop moving. To start them following you again simply move back in to range of them.\n5. The females will spawn in the same area every time, see map.\n6. The pairs are as follows\n      - Blue - Sky\n      - Cod - Fish\n      - Heat - Fire\n      - Moon - Star\n      - Orange - Apple\n      - Rain - Cloud\n      - Snow - White\n      - Song - Sound\n7. The mission is completed upon speaking to Rhap Nelhah and choosing to finish.\n   - Alternatively, if all 8 matches are made, the mission will complete automatically.\n8. The Rune of Release spawns at the starting NPC, Rhap Nelhah.\n9. The map below is awesome. Use it.',
        notes = '1. Vulcanian Bombs cast Fire-based magic of the appropriate level.\n2. Vulcanian Bombs aggro sight and magic.  They can be avoided with Invisible (Status).\n   - Apkallus will continue to follow you while you are Invisible.',
    },
    ['Apkallu Seizure'] = {
        id = 46,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Ilrusi Atoll',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Capture the apkallu',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'To win this assault, herd 1 or more Fairy Apkallu to Clavauert B Chanoix for his Lebros Apkallu Brothel.\nIn order to herd a Fairy Apkallu, a complicated courting process must be followed:\n1. First, obtain a Hamsi by finding and clicking on one of the many ??? that are scattered about the map.\n2. Once you have a delicious fish, find a passive Fairy Apkallu.  Stand in front of it at a medium-short distance, close enough to select the target.\n3. The Apkallu will stop and stare at you, and you will receive the message "The Fairy Apkallu is staring at you"\n4. /bow to the Apkallu.\n   - One of two things will happen:\n     - "The Fairy Apkallu is wary of your presence"; repeat the process again.\n     - "The Fairy Apkallu seems curious about you"; repeat the process again.\n5. If you receive the message that the Apkallu "let down its guard", immediately use the /welcome motion.\n   - If the Apkallu says it likes you, you then have one second to click the Apkallu to give it the Hamsi.\n     - If done successfully, you will get the message "You successfully capture the Fairy Apkallu!".  When this happens, quickly circle directly behind the Apkallu, and stand about 3 Yalms away directly behind the Fairy Apkallu.\n     - NOTE: Apkallu\'s that "liked" you will not give this message again for the duration of the assault. It will keep saying "It\'s wary of you" but you can keep giving it Hamsi until the captured mode. In other words, you can\'t feed Hamsi to an Apkallu until it has been allowed  after the first "it likes you" message, then it can be fed Hamsi anytime when it stares at you. You will not get another "it likes you" message if you try to redo the /bow and /welcome reactions because it already likes you to begin with (Useful if you failed to /welcome quick enough or this Apkallu ran away and are attempting to recapture).\n6. The Fairy Apkallu will slowly waddle towards the Professor.  Stay a few yalms directly behind the Fairy Apkallu.  If it turns, as it will near the Professor, make sure you adjust to stay directly behind it.  Be careful of cliffs; the Apkallu will go straight up while you will need to quickly navigate the cliff.\n7. If the Fairy Apkallu sees any Kelp Pugil, it will flee. If you are quick, you can immediately recapture it sometimes by running behind it and clicking it again.\n8. If you leave the "safe zone" behind the Apkallu, it will stop.  If you do not return quickly to the position behind the Apkallu, it will run away and the courting process will need to be repeated.\n   - You will need to click another ??? for a new Hamsi if it runs away.\n   - DO NOT GO INTO FIRST-PERSON MODE! There are two hills next to the start quest NPC that require third-person mode in order to traverse if approaching from the left-hand side (if looking at the NPC). Far better strategy is to just lock on the Apkallu and position your self accordingly and when you have to run around terrain; unlock , run around terrain, re-lock, and reposition.\nHerding a single Fairy Apkallu will cause the Rune of Release to spawn at the professor.  Capturing more Apkallu will increase the amount of points earned, to a maximum of 1333 with 3 people.',
        notes = '1. Kelp Pugil are very weak and can be killed solo or duo with ease.\n2. Kelp Pugil do not respawn.\n3. Movement speed seems to negatively affect interactions with the Apkallu.  It is suggested that you remove all forms of movement speed + for this assault.',
    },
    ['Azure Ailments'] = {
        id = 19,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Gather pathological data',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
