        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Defeat Count Dracula.',
        notes = '1. Count Dracula is a Dark Knight. While he hits really hard he only moves at regular speed and has horrible pathing, if you get in trouble kiting is incredibly easy. He also stops frequently to cast tier 2 nukes and absorb spells.\n2. TP moves are as follows\n      - Bloodrake: Single target drain attack. Multiple hits and absorbable by 3 shadows.  Does around 1000-1500 damage on a WAR/NIN without full shadows up.\n      - Decollation: Medium physical conal damage.\n      - Eternal Damnation: Line attack Doom, gaze attack, removable with Cursna. Also removable with Holy Water.\n      - Heliovoid: AoE Status drain, drains 1 effect, including food, from everybody within range. Note that if he absorbs counterstance his counters will not show in the chat log.\n      - Nocturnal Servitude: Conal Charm, turns those affected into bats. Seems to last around a minute.\n      - Nosferatu\'s Kiss: AoE HP and TP drain. After using this weapon skill a Cursed Doppelganger will be summoned, copying the target of Nosferatu\'s Kiss. The Doppelganger will look like the target including weapons/armour. The weapons of the target and its job traits will be shared by the Doppelganger. The Doppelganger will use weaponskills based upon the weapons of the target, including relic WS if relevant.\n      - Wings of Gehenna: AoE damage, knockback and stun. Wipes shadows.',
    },
    ['Breaking Morale'] = {
        id = 14,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Steal the supplies',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Quick Completion: Exit the tunnel, turn left and go up the ramp. Grab the 1st chest at I-7 and return to the NPC to turn in. Talk to NPC again to "give up" and the Rune of Release will spawn.\nThe object of this assault is to collect treasure from coffers scattered about the map and return them to the start NPC Quhaaja without being detected by the roaming Mamool Ja.\n1. There are 8 total coffers containing supplies; only one must be successfully retrieved to win the assault.\n2. Bringing more supplies to the start NPC increases the point reward.\n3. In the main area of the assault there are many Trainers (blue mages) and Recruits (orange melees) Mamool Ja that must be avoided.\n4. Refer to the map for the locations of the treasure coffers.\n5. It is possible to carry more than one supply at a time.  However, if captured, all supplies will be returned to their original coffers.\nWhen the party is satisfied with the number of supplies retrieved, talk to the NPC and confirm to spawn the Rune of Release.\n6. Once the Rune of Release is spawned, the NPC will not accept any more supplies.\n7. It takes about 5 seconds for the Rune of Release to spawn, so make sure not to leave the confirmation process too late.\nThe base AP rewarded for this assault is 800 plus 66 points per supply retrieved, for a maximum of 1333 with all 8 coffers retrieved.',
        notes = '1. The Mamool Ja move around very frequently, making it difficult to avoid aggro.\n2. If a Mamool Ja Trainer spots a player, the player will be instantly warped to the dead-end at I-8.  Any supplies he was carrying will be confiscated and returned to their original coffer.\n3. If a Mamool Ja Recruit spots a player, they will attack the player.  They can be slept and lose aggro very quickly.  They are Thief and occasionally Triple Attack.\n4. Mamool Ja link and detect by sight.  Thus, if you have a Recruit slept and a Trainer sees it, the player will instantly be spotted, even if the Trainer cannot see the player directly.\n5. One-shotting Mamool Ja does not allow them to detect you and it is very easy to cut a path with high-tier nukes.',
    },
    ['Building Bridges'] = {
