        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The goal of this assault is to use an Automaton to destroy shipwrecks scattered about the area.\n1. There are five ship wrecks. See the map for more details.\n2. To be assigned an automaton, talk to the starting NPC.\n   - The party can only have one automaton.\n   - The person who talks to the starting NPC will be designated the automaton\'s master.\n3. The automaton will follow its master around until it finds wreckage to demolish.\n4. Only the automaton can attack the wreckage.  However, you can use AoE abilities and spells on targets near adjacent wreckage to cause damage to the wreckage.\n5. Each time the automaton uses a weaponskill on a wreckage, a Carrion Crab will spawn and attack the automaton.\n   - The crab cannot be distracted from the automaton.  However, the automaton can be cured and crabs only have about 2000 hp.\n6. If the automaton is killed or despawns due to its master dying, a new one can be obtained by talking to the start NPC again.\n7. If the automaton is damaged, the party can opt to repair the automaton at the start NPC.\n8. After the wreckages are demolished, talk to the starting NPC to spawn the Rune of Release\n9. Fastest way to complete is to just pull imps and do AOE damage such as -ga or -ja spells. Don\'t even need the automation alive but you do need to talk to the starter NPC first to start the assault which gives you a free one anyway.',
        notes = '1. Crabs will always have hate on the automaton.',
