        walkthrough = 'To win this assault, subdue at least one Lamia or Merrow by breaking its weapon.\n1. Weapons can sometimes be broken using critical-hit weaponskills and critical hits.\n   - At iLvl, a Dual Wield job like Red Mage with Haste II/Temper II/etc and two DMG1 daggers would usually break the weapons in about 10 seconds.\n2. Once the Lamia or Merrow has been disarmed, it will immediately surrender, becoming an NPC.\n3. There are 12 Lamia and Merrow.\n   - The mission can be completed at any time after the first successful subdual by talking to the NPC at the start.  Subduing more monsters will result in a higher point reward.\n   - Once all 12 have been killed or subdued, the Rune of Release will automatically spawn if at least one has been subdued.\nThe Rune of Release will spawn at the starting NPC.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Desperately Seeking Cephalopods'] = {
        id = 49,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Ilrusi Atoll',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'To increase production of special nighttime camouflage, the Imperial marines require large quantities of a secretion from a rare cephalopod known as the ahtapot, found in the Ilrusi Atoll.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Have two or three people fishing at a time, if you can handle it, fish at different NPCs, or have other party members out at other NPCs.\n2. Once the NPC dialog changes, finding the proper NPC is priority.\n3. You can fish up the Orobon without NPC text changing. People have been lucky and fished up only after finding the proper NPC, but without details.\n4. Kill the Orobon',
        notes = '1. The Qiqirn Pecheur in this zone all drop a Willow Fishing Rod or a Fly Lure, but given the time constraint and uncertainty of fishing up the Orobon, it is highly suggested to bring your own rod and lure/bait.\n2. The goal of this assault is to fish up an Orobon NM and return the item you receive to the NPC at the start.\n3. Fishing at any point in the map will net one of the following monsters: Orobon, Pugil, Pugil, Crab, Kraken. It all depends on luck\n      - It is possible that the first thing you fish at the starting point can be the Orobon (verified, first hand encounter).\n4. No fishing skill is needed.\n5. The Orobon will only be fished at a certain point on the map.\n6. There are 4 NPC fisherman also on the map. At first they will be dismissive toward you. Once you fish up 4 or 5 enemies, they will change text.\n7. NPC speech will read along the lines of either "this area is no good" or "I\'ve got a good feeling about this area."\n   - Only one NPC will say they like their area, continue fishing at this NPC.\n8. After 4 or 5 more enemies fished, the NPC will start giving more specific locations, something along the lines of "to the North is a good spot."\n9. The Orobon has a fairly large amount of HP, plus usual Orobon moves that can silence, plague, slow, and other nasty debuffs.\n10. Whomever deals the killing blow will automatically receive the athapot to return to the NPC.',
    },
    ['Egg Conservation'] = {
        id = 28,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Lebros Cavern',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Drive out the hunters',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Destroy the Qiqirn while keeping the Apkallu healed.\n1. All Apkallu are curable and buffable.\n2. Smaller apkallu are female.  They will not aid the players.\n   - The assault is a failure if all female Apkallu are defeated.\n3. Larger apkallu are male.  They will automatically attack any nearby Qiqirn.\n   - If they are damaged beyond 50%, they will fall over and stop aiding the party.\n4. Qiqirn will slowly approach in pairs or solo from the east and west side; player should not stray too far from the gaggle of apkallus.\n5. Drag the Qiqirn through the middle of the pack of Apkallu to get the male Apkallu assisting in the fight.\nThe Rune of Release will spawn at (I-8) when all of the Qiqirn are defeated.',
        notes = '1. As thieves, Qiqirn Egglers are highly evasive, attack quickly and can Triple Attack.',
    },
    ['Escort Professor Chanoix'] = {
        id = 3,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Protect the Professor',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Guide and protect Professor Clavauert B Chanoix to the room at (J-5) or (G-9).\n      - Once entering the Assault, the Professor will begin to move once someone moves past him. There is no need to interact with him to make him move. Likewise, he will not stop moving once he starts.\n      - All enemies in the Assault can aggro the Professor if he gets too close to them.\n      - It is recommended to run ahead of the Professor to defeat enemies before they aggro him.\n      - The Professor does not have a lot of HP. You are able to heal him using Cure spells. However, you are unable to use any party-specific healing spells such as Magic Fruit or Curing Waltz. You may also cast Protect and Shell on him.\n      - Occasionally, the Professor will take a break and stop moving at certain intervals. You make take this time to heal him or yourself.\n      - While you may avoid aggro with Sneak, the Professor will continue to aggro enemies.\n      - As all enemies in the Assault are Undead, you may aggro with low HP (yellow or red HP).\n      - Gelid Bhoots will often cast Blizzaga III which can be dangerous to the Professor and your party.\n      - The Assault will be automatically failed if Clavauert B Chanoix is defeated.',
        notes = '1. All enemies are susceptible to Light-based Sleep, such as Sheep Song and Lullaby. Also susceptible to Weight and Bind.',
    },
    ['Evade and Escape'] = {
        id = 24,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Lebros Cavern',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Discover alternate route',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Simultaneously activate the three switches.\n1. The switches will be up in 3 of a possible 7 locations. Each of the possible locations are at the dead-ends on the extremeties of the map.\n      - Once hit, switches will stay active for 5 minutes.\n      - Switches do not appear on Wide Scan.\n2. The Rune of Release will appear in the cave at (H-8) after the switches have been activated simultaneously.\nFor solo i119 players;\n3. Locate the switches first, killing Dahak as you go.\n4. Activate the switches, furthest away first, working your way back towards the Rune of Release.',
        notes = '1. The Dahaks have a very narrow vision and in the wider tunnels it is possible to avoid agro by standing on the walls as they run by.\n2. The Dahaks have extremely high HP and are thus more trouble than they\'re worth to kill (although they are trivial for an i119 player).\n3. Wide Scan is useful for avoiding Dahak agro.',
    },
    ['Excavation Duty'] = {
        id = 21,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Lebros Cavern',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Protect the Professor',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Destroy all 5 of the Brittle rocks.\n1. Brittle Rocks can be destroyed through damage, and damage over time is a very good way to do it. SCH/BLM can cast Bio, three non-overlapping elemental DoTs (e.g. Shock, Burn, Choke), and Helix. Immune to Poison II\n2. Volcanic Bombs aggro sight and can be completely avoided with Invisible (Status).\n3. Qiqirn Volcanists and Ceramists will occasionally drop Qiqirn Mine Temporary Items to help destroy the rocks.\n   - Once you have obtained a mine, engage a Brittle Rock and use the temporary item.  Stay engaged until the device detonates and the rock will be destroyed in a single blast.\n   - At Item Level 117+, you can kill Qiqirn way faster than the walls, so it\'s worth trying to get bombs from them. Be sure to only kill one at a time.\n4. The Rune of Release will spawn at the dead end room at (F-10) when the last Brittle Rock is defeated.\n   - In order to save time, a party member can be sent towards the Rune while the last Brittle Rock is being fought.',
        notes = '1. Brittle Rocks take drastically reduced damage from all sources except dots, which are a very effective way to damage them.\n2. Brittle Rocks do not attack or move.\n3. Brittle Rocks are not in fact brittle.\n4. Brittle Rocks will not be destroyed by mines if you are not attacking the rock when it explodes, and you will lose the mine.',
    },
