    ['Golden Salvage'] = {
        id = 41,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Ilrusi Atoll',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Recover the figurehead',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. 12 coffers are scattered about the map, 3 in each of the 4 paths.\n2. One of them contains the figurehead; the other 11 are mimics which will attack you when you investigate the coffer.\n3. It is impossible to run from a mimic if you have hate.\n   - However, if the mimic has hate on a pet and the rest of its targets get out of range, it will deaggro when the pet dies or is unsummoned.\n4. Once the correct chest is found, the Rune of Release spawns at the start.',
        notes = '1. Cursed Chests will look and act like normal coffers until aggroed.\n2. Cursed Chests are immobile and will draw in its target.\n   - If all of its targets are beyond draw-in range, it will deaggro and revert to looking like a normal coffer.',
    },
    ['Imperial Agent Rescue'] = {
        id = 11,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Rescue the Agent',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The objective of this assault is to rescue the NPC Brujeel by tricking the Mamool Ja into breaking the impassable gates.\n1. There are 3 gates, as marked on the map.  The NPC is trapped in a pot beyond one of the 3 gates.\n2. You may pull Mamool Ja from the surrounding area to attempt to break the gate.\n      - The Mamool Ja come in 3 flavors: WHM, BST, and NIN.\n3. To break the gate, you must trick the Mamool Ja into hitting it.\n      - Mamools must be facing the gate.\n         - Their moves may miss the gate even when used while facing it.\n      - One weapon throw (Axe Throw or Staff Toss) that successfully hits the gate will break the gate instantly.\n         - Ninja Mamool Ja don\'t have a weapon-throw technique, and thus are less efficient for breaking down gates.\n      - Four Firespits will also break it down.\n4. Once a gate breaks, click on the Pot Hatch to open the cage.\n      - If you are lucky, Brujeel will appear after a moment, and then Warp to safety. Since naturally you can only cast Warp if you are not trapped behind an unlocked pot hatch.\n5. If the pot is empty, move on to another gate.\nThe Rune of Release will appear in the dead end room at (J-8) after Brujeel is "rescued".',
        notes = 'There seems to be a bug with pets that prevents the gate from being broken. If you\'re having trouble getting the gate to break, try dismissing your pet.',
    },
    ['Imperial Code'] = {
        id = 8,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Retrieve the OGMA',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. You must defeat 3 NIN NMs: Oko, Danzo and Saizo. They will each leave behind a ??? after their corpse has faded, the last of which will be the OGMA, which when retrieved will spawn the Rune of Release.\n   - Oko and Danzo both dual wield katanas, while Saizo uses a great katana and can also use Mijin Gakure. Oko and Saizo both have a Kusa very nearby them, which you should probably attempt to pull first if you don\'t have a way to sleep the Kusa.\n2. The Rune of Release will spawn on the border of (G-8) and (H-8) on the lower level. It will be right under a drop-down from the top level.',
        notes = '1. The 3 NMs and the Kusa are humanoid ninjas, they will self buff with utsusemi while idle, cast ninjutsu and use Katana or Great Katana Weaponskills. They aggro true sight.\n2. All mobs in this assault seem to resist drain type effects.\n3. Kusa are susceptible to lullaby and other light-based sleeps.\n4. The Kudagitsunes are Bhoots, which are aggressive to sound and low health. On aggro they will immediately use Perdition if you are in range; Perdition range seems to be about 10\'. If you are out of range they will cast a spell, then use Perdition once in range.\n   - Perdition is an instant death ability that can kill you even if you are high level!',
    },
    ['Imperial Treasure Retrieval'] = {
        id = 16,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Recover the treasure',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The objective of this assault is to return at least 1 gem to the start NPC, Zahakahm.  While it is very easy to win this assault, it is very difficult to maximize AP return due to the mechanics of the assault, which is built like a game of tag.\n1. The Mamool Ja Savage\'s team is comprised of:\n   - Mamool Ja Governor\n   - Red Badge Mamool Ja\n   - Blue Badge Mamool Ja\n   - Yellow Badge Mamool Ja\n   - Green Badge Mamool Ja\n   - White Badge Mamool Ja\n   - Black Badge Mamool Ja\n2. Gems can be found in coffers scattered about the map.\n3. When you are carrying a gem you are vulnerable to be "tagged" by Mamool Ja.\n4. When tagged, the Mamool Ja will take your gem and you will respawn at the start NPC.\n5. When you are not carrying a gem, you can tag a Mamool Ja who is carrying a gem.\n6. When you tag a Mamool Ja, you will take its gem and it will respawn at F-7 where their base and NPC Mamool Ja Governor are.\n7. Speaking to the NPC Mamool Ja Governor will return you to the starting point and cause a gem you hold to be taken.\n8. Zone-wide information will be given whenever a jewel is obtained, stolen, or returned to each teams NPC.\nOnce all the gems are returned to either your base or the Mamool Ja base a zone message states "You have recovered all the treasure".  Speak to the start NPC Zahakahm at any point after returning at least 1 gem to spawn the Rune of Release.\nBase AP is calculated as 200 + 133 per gem returned.  It is not currently known how many gems there are, however data suggests 9 Coffers total.',
        notes = nil,
    },
