    ['Operation: Black Pearl'] = {
        id = 29,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Lebros Cavern',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Rescue Princess Kadjaya',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The objective of this assault is to prevent the NPCs Princess Kadjaya and her escort, Whyjham, from taking even a single hit before the Troll NM Jorporbor the Hellraker is defeated.\n1. If Princess Kadjaya is attacked, the mission automatically fails.\n2. Two waves of monsters will slowly approach the center from the three tunnels leading from the center area.\n   - The pattern of monsters is the same for each wave:  Wamouracampa x5, followed by Crimson Eruca x5, followed by Vulcanian Bomb x5, followed by Troll Combatant x1.\n   - At the end of each wave of monsters is a single even-match Troll Combatant.  The Troll has higher HP and is more dangerous than the other monsters.\n   - It is possible for both waves of monsters to approach from the same tunnel.\n     - Monsters that would normally link with each other will not if they are part of different waves in the same tunnel.\n3. When a Troll Combatant is killed, all living monsters in its wave will immediately despawn.\n   - After a Troll is killed, a new wave will immediately spawn.\n4. An easy way to win solo is to kill all of the enemies of the first wave except for the troll, which you will kite around. You can then go snipe the troll of each single wave (clearing the whole wave) until the NM pops.\n5. The three tunnels leading to the center where Princess Kadjaya stands are guarded by NPCs: Yanshaal, Djahama, and Kudjreel.\n   - The NPCs guarding the tunnel entrances will warn you of monsters approaching from their respective tunnels.\n   - If monsters reach the guard, he will be defeated in a single hit, and can no longer warn of approaching monsters in his tunnel.\n   - The number of remaining guards at the end of the assault affects the amount of AP awarded.\n6. Jorporbor the Hellraker will remain hidden until several sets of waves of monsters have been defeated.\n   - Waves of other monsters will continue to approach Princess Kadjaya after Jorporbor the Hellraker has attacked.\nThe mission is won once Jorporbor the Hellraker is defeated.  Any remaining monsters will disappear and the Rune of Release will appear at Princess Kadjaya.',
        notes = '1. Except for the Trolls (around 4-5k HP), the monsters in this assault have extremely low HP (~300) and can be killed using AoE weaponskills.\n2. The Vulcanian Bombs can cast Flare.\n3. The Troll Combatants are sleepable, and the next wave will not spawn until it is defeated.  It is possible to keep one slept and then only have to deal with one wave at a time.',
    },
    ['Operation: Snake Eyes'] = {
        id = 38,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Periqia',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Locate the generals',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'This assault is composed of several tasks which must all be completed to unlock the Rune of Release.\nTask 1: Kill the Qutrub\n1. Scattered about the start location (I-9) are 5 Qutrub.  Defeat these to unlock the doors to the north.\nTask 2: Kill Merrow No.16\n2. In one of the 6 rooms to the north, Merrow No 16 will be fighting general Karazahm.  Defeat Merrow No.16 and do not let the general die.\n3. Merrow No 16 and the general do not show up on wide scan, so you will need to check each room quickly to find them.\nTask 3: Kill Lamia No.14\n4. In (I-6), Lamia No 14 must be defeated to unlock the door to the north.\n5. Beware of Belly Dance, a sight-based AoE charm.  Everyone should face away from the NM when she uses this ability to avoid being charmed.\n(Another strategy for #14 is for the entire party to get charmed, #14 then will proceed to take the whole party through the gate and drop you right near general Umarid. You may/may not have to kill #14 depending on how your party uncharms. If you choose to fight her at the general then make sure everyone faces her and keep bio/poison on in case the party gets charmed because she will regen when unclaimed. (She seems to use belly dance a lot less when fought near the general))\nTask 4: Kill Lamia No.17\n6. In (H-6), you will find general Umarid.  Upon approaching him, he will attack.  Damage him to <50% HP and Lamia No 17 will appear.\n7. The general has approximately 5300 HP.\n   - Do not kill the general\n   - General has less than 4463 HP with single person entry at 119. 1 Subduction did kill them.\n8. Once Lamia No.17 appears, defeat her to unlock the Rune of Release at (I-5).',
        notes = '1. Merrow Shadowdancer can be avoided with Invisible (Status).',
    },
    ['Orichalcum Survey'] = {
        id = 2,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Discover Orichalcum Ore',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The goal of this Assault is to mine up an Orichalcum Ore from the mining points scattered around the map. The mined ore is a temporary item (You may not use a real ore in your inventory to complete this Assault). As soon as the ore has been mined up the Qiqirns will switch from being NPCs to aggressive monsters (You can avoid aggroing Qiqirns by using Invisible).\n1. To begin the Assault speak to Mulwahah (H-8) and he will give you a Pickaxe temporary item (Normal pickaxes cannot be used for this assault).\n      - Unlike a normal Pickaxe where it must be traded to to the Mining Point, you may simply interact (i.e. talk) to the Mining Point.\n2. Search for a Mining Point and interact with it. One of the following will occur:\n      - You obtain an Orichalcum Ore.\n      - You mine up a Pebble or Zinc Ore which will then be placed in the party\'s treasure pool.\n      - You are unable to mine anything.\n      - Your Pickaxe breaks. You will need to return to Mulwahah to obtain a new one.\n      - A Mineral Worm spawns with aggro. Mineral Worms have very low HP but decent attack. You may run out of its attack and casting range and continue looking for more mining points. However, they must be defeated to access the same mining point (Note: The defeated worm must despawn until the mining point can be mined from again).\n3. When an Orichalcum Ore has been obtained all Qiqirn Miners will become hostile. It is recommended to put up Invisible at this point and run back to Mulwahah. Once the person with the Orichalcum Ore has spoken to him the Assault will be completed.',
        notes = '1. Mineral Worms have a chance of spawning upon an unsuccessful mining attempt.\n2. Qiqirn Miners will become hostile after an Orichalcum Ore has been mined.',
    },
    ['Preemptive Strike'] = {
        id = 12,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Destroy the assassins',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The object to this assault is to eliminate all of the Mamool Ja Executioners.\n1. There are 13 Mamool Ja, of jobs BLU, WHM, and NIN.\n2. The puks need not be defeated.\nOnce all the Mamool Ja are dead, the Rune of Release will spawn in the dead end room within the southeast corner of (I-7).\nNote: Players without a ranged attack or magic should not fall down from the starting ledge before defeating the Mamools at (I-8) and (G-8) as there is no ramp back up to this first ledge.\nThe easiest order to pull is as follows:\n:1) BLU right in front of you as you exit cave.\n:2) BLU and/or WHM east of the middle hill, sometimes they are closer to the middle hill than the eastern ledge, pull as needed.\n:3) BLU and/or WHM east of the middle hill, sometimes they are closer to the middle hill than the eastern ledge, pull as needed.\n:4) South of middle hill, there is a WHM.\n:5) Keep going clockwise around the hill and you\'ll find a NIN to the north.\n:6) BLU and WHM west of central hill underneath the bridge.\n:7) BLU and WHM west of central hill underneath the bridge.\n:8) BLU to the south once you cross the bridge to the west.\n:9) NIN either on the ledge or on the ground to the north of the western bridge.\n:10) NIN and WHM together across the canyon and under a hut from the western bridge. Pull one at a time, they link by sight. Watch for Puk aggro.\n:11) NIN and WHM together across the canyon and under a hut from the western bridge. Pull one at a time, they link by sight. Watch for Puk aggro.\n:12) BLU north of the hut where NIN and WHM were.\n:13) BLU near the Rune of Release at (I-8), a little to the south and up on a ledge, can be a tricky pull since he often walks out of sight.',
        notes = '1. Puk Executioners are susceptible to charm.\n2. Because the Mamools do provide EXP when they are killed, you can expect to make 1100-1300 EXP per run, assuming Sanction and 3 members',
    },
    ['Red Versus Blue'] = {
        id = 9,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Defeat Raubahn',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The assault is won once Raubahn dies, there are various ways to accomplish this, but as a rule you should have somebody looking after the NPCs, particularly the Hume NPC.',
        notes = '1. The Immortals and Raubahn will not spawn until you talk to the Captain NPC at the start, they will spawn at the top of (I-6).\n2. If the Hume Captain NPC, Shailham, is defeated you lose the assault immediately.\n3. You lose points for each of your red team NPCs that are defeated.\n4. All of your NPCs are Black Mages, all of the Immortals are Blue Mages and cast spells accordingly.\n5. The two teams are comprised of the following NPC\'s:\n   - Red Team, the Inexorables.\n     - Shailham: Captain\n     - Dhiadjhar, Zhadjaraf, Ganmuul, Jalyaat, Rahdjab, Ghahnis, Tahbmar, Rhushouf.\n   - Blue Team, the Immortals.\n     - Raubahn: Captain\n     - Ghayaraan, Krinahal, Varajahl, Mareyamad, Shayaam, Habraheem, Qudeen, Salyhaar.\n     - Sharayaan, Ubdeen, Bashdeel, Wharadi, Hkadouf, Afrhaad, Nareema, Udhaaman, Yhalbin.',
    },
