    ['Sagelord Elimination'] = {
        id = 13,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Defeat Sagelord Molaal Ja',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The object of this assault is to hunt down Sagelord Molaal Ja and damage him until he is forced to warp out.\n1. The area of this assault is filled with Mamool Ja Trainees that will aggro and link to Molaal Ja.\n2. When Molaal Ja links Trainees, they will only initially be aware of the target that Molaal Ja currently hates.\n   - The Trainees will not deaggro naturally, but if nobody acts upon them, they will go passive when they kill their only target.\n   - While not too dangerous individually, the swarm of Trainees caused by a fleeing Molaal Ja can cause a wipe.  Make sure to use Reraise (Status) in the event of a wipe.\n   - Assigning someone to preemptively aggro and kite Trainees (especially someone with movement speed enhancement) will prevent Molaal Ja from linking anything when he runs away.\n3. Using a pet (such as Carbuncle) or Widescan can help the party locate Molaal Ja quickly when he runs away.\nOnce Molaal Ja reaches 15% HP, he will Warp and the Rune of Release will spawn in the dead end room within the southeast corner of (I-7).',
        notes = '1. After being damaged, Molaal Ja will disengage from battle and flee away for a period of time.\n2. Molaal Ja will not regenerate HP, even if he goes passive with no DoT spells.\n3. If you can damage Molaal Ja sufficiently right away, he will warp out right away and not flee.',
    },
    ['Saving Private Ryaaf'] = {
        id = 33,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Periqia',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Find the survivors',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The mission is a man.\n1. You begin the assault at (I-7), which is also where the Rune of Release spawns.\n2. The goal is to rescue the 3 captured NPCs while avoiding the fomors and chigoes.\n      - The NPCs are hidden in the 4 side rooms and the middle. They will be seen as a hunched over figure in a black cloak, which will only turn into an NPC or a fomor when you move up to it. Note that there are other ways to tell the difference between an NPC and a fomor, as shown below.\n3. Your group should have a way of dealing with the three cursed chigoes in each room. While possible to pull these one by one with care, you will often end up with all three at once. Having a way to sleep these as well as somebody who can easily dispatch with chigoes is recommended for this. You can also sleep the chigoes, check whether the npc is a fomor or an npc and run away while they are still asleep.\n4. There are only 5 possible position combinations for the hunched over NPC/fomors to appear in.\n5. You can distinguish between NPCs and Fomors initially by the direction the hunched over figure is facing, except in the East room.\n      - Fomors will always be facing East.',
        notes = '1. Experimental Undead agro to true sound and abilities.\n2. Cursed Chigoes agro to true sound and true sight.\n3. Cursed Chigoes have additional effect: Curse.\n4. It is very easy to lose agro on mobs in this assault, especially with movement speed+.\n5. Cursed Chigoes may be one shot killed with a critical hit, job ability or AoE Weaponskill.',
    },
    ['Seagull Grounded'] = {
        id = 31,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Periqia',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Escort the prisoner',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The objective to this mission is to escort the prisoner Excaliace to where the Rune of Release spawns at (F-12).\n1. Excaliace will move automatically when a party member is a few yards behind him.\n   - Excaliace will stop at certain points if party members are crowding him and remark, "Someone\'s been eating too much garlic..."\n   - If no party members are close to Excaliace, he try to escape by running away, "Now\'s my chance!"  If he is successful, the mission is a failure.\n   - If Excaliace encounters a monster, he will run away.\n2. Excaliace will investigate one room labeled \'A\', one room labeled \'B\', and one room labeled \'C\' on the map below.\n   - If the room contains Arrapago Crabs, you must defeat the crabs before he enters the room.\n3. At the junction in (H-8), Excaliace will choose to go towards the label \'D\' or the label \'E\'.  In either case, the path ahead of him will contain 2 or 3 Periqia Pugils and possibly a Debaucher which need to be cleared.\n4. In (G-10) there is a Debaucher which needs to be taken care of.  It is possible to pull the Debaucher to the side so that Excaliace can pass by while the party deals with the monster.\n5. In the final room there is a Debaucher.  It can be pulled away so that Excaliace does not see it.\n6. The Rune of Release spawns in the northwest corner of the room, where Excaliace completes his patrol.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Searat Salvation'] = {
        id = 45,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Ilrusi Atoll',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Save the Qiqirn Divers',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'The goal of this assault is to guide 1 or more NPC Qiqirn Divers from the start point at (F-10) to the Qiqirn Chief Diver at (J-6)\n1. Talking to a Qiqirn Diver will induce it to follow you.\n2. A single player can lead multiple Qiqirn Divers simultaneously.\n3. NPCs named Giant Orobons patrol the map looking for tasty Qiqirns to eat.\n   - Don\'t let your Qiqirns get eaten.\n4. If an Orobon sees a Qiqirn, they will give chase and the Qiqirn will stop following the player and run away for a short time at enhanced speed.\n5. If your Qiqirns get scared off, click on them to induce them to follow you again.\n6. Bringing at least 1 Qiqirn Diver to the Chief Diver will spawn the Rune of Release.\n   - Bringing multiple Qiqirn Divers will result in a higher score, up to a maximum of 1166 points for all 5 Qiqirns escorted with 3 people.\n     - 916 Points for bringing 3 Quqirn Divers with 3 or less participants.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Shanarha Grass Conservation'] = {
        id = 4,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Protect the vegetation.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Defeat all 20 Conies.\n      - You begin at (I-9) as do all 20 Conies. Shortly after the Assault begins they will split and start moving either north or south.\n      - Sometimes the Conies will run away while engaged, eventually losing aggro. Note that if they run past other Conies they will link. If a Coney runs away and loses aggro, if left unclaimed they will recover to full HP.\n      - It is recommended to wait a few minutes after the Assault begins to allow the Conies to spread out and avoid a mass link.\n      - Once a Coney reaches a vegetation they will eat it until it disappears. The Assault is automatically failed if too much vegetation is eaten.\n      - Assault Points are based on the number of vegetation remaining. The more vegetation remaining at the end of the Assault will reward more Assault Points.',
        notes = '1. The Conies do not aggro.\n2. The Conies link by sight. Because the Conies are grouped together at the start of the Assault, it is possible to cause a mass link.\n3. Similarly to the Rabbits in Uleguerand Range the Conies will use Snow Cloud rather than Dust Cloud, which inflict Paralyze rather than Blind.\n4. The Conies do not appear on Widescan.',
    },
    ['Shooting Down the Baron'] = {
        id = 34,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Periqia',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Eliminate the Black Baron',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Shoot down The Red Black Baron.\n1. You will enter the Assault on the east side of the map in the room at (I-8). This is also where the Rune of Release spawns.\n2. The Black Baron will not appear on Widescan.\n3. A short time after he is engaged the Baron will warp away to a different part of the map. For this reason having a job that can summon a pet to follow him to his next location is extremely useful, as it will save a lot of time. /SMN is also fine for this.  It should be noted that at ilvl 119 the Black Baron dies in one weaponskill.  The pet strategy is no longer necessary.\n4. While he has significantly more HP, he is otherwise pretty much the same as a regular VT Imp.',
        notes = '1. The Periqia Pugils are scattered around the middle of the map, they are true sound.\n2. The Black Baron will spawn randomly in one of several locations around the map, either in the middle area or within the NW, NE, SW, or SE tunnels.',
    },
    ['Siegemaster Assassination'] = {
        id = 25,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Lebros Cavern',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Assassinate Borgerlur',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Eliminate Borgerlur, he is disguised as one of the Old Trolls.\n1. Trolls will repop very quickly, try to keep track of which are repops and which are originals. Note that the Borgerlur Troll will never change and once defeated the rest will despawn and the assault will end.\n2. There appears to be some strange behaviour surrounding the Borgerlur troll and also repops. Respawned mobs will have hate on the the target of the Borgerlur Troll if it is engaged.\n3. Repops will now auto agro (this seems to be a recent change)\n4. Repop time is 3 mins 45 seconds\n5. Once Borgerlur is defeated the Rune of Release will spawn at (G-7).',
        notes = '1. Troll ranged attacks are fire-based and will hit through shadows.\n2. Every troll will use Eagle Eye Shot, which will also go through shadows, however note that it is a physical attack. It will deal significantly more damage with abilities like Berserk and Counterstance.',
