    ['Supplies Recovery'] = {
        id = 6,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Leujaoam Sanctum',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Retrieve the supplies',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. The goal of the assault is to collect more supplies than the immortals.\n   - Supplies are temporary items dropped from Imps.\n2. Imps will not appear anywhere on the map until one player talks to the NPC Kuihlud at the start.\n3. An Immortal can stop you from getting supplies if they perform an action against an imp.\n4. The Immortal can get the supplies even if your party kills the Imp.\n   - Not all Imps drop supplies.\nWhen you obtain supplies it is displayed in the chat log as a temporary item.\n5. The chat log will regularly display how many supplies have been collected by the Immortals.\n6. The mission ends when all Imps on the map have been defeated.\n7. If you have more supplies than the Immortals, you win.\n8. If you have less than or an equal number of supplies as the Immortals, you lose.\n9. The Rune of Release will appear next to Kuihlud back at the start point.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Double Agent'] = {
        id = 15,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Mamool Ja Training Grounds',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Apprehend the spy',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Your role in this mission is to find and capture the Qiqirn who is the spy. He looks and talks like every other qiqirn, but using information given to you by other Qiqirn, you can deduce which one he is.\n1. There are many Qiqirn Spy (NPC) spread over the whole map, and many Puks too. The Puk are agressive, so it is advised you are able to sleep, charm, or have another method of distracting them.\n2. Talking to the Qiqirn Spy gives 3 options\n      - Capture\n      - Talk\n      - Nothing\n3. The Qiqirn always tell the truth, except for the spy.  If they point you in the direction of the spy, listen to their advice.\n4. The directions Qiqirn can give you are :\n      - Should be close\n      - Should be far\n      -  amount of Yalms away\n      - Some Qiqirns can be completely oblivious to where the spy is and not know anything at all\n5. The easiest way to tell which one is the liar, is to talk to multiple NPCs in an area. If all of them are consistent except one, the one will most likely be the spy. For example, if all the Qiqirn say "Should be near", and "It is to the east", when only one says "To the west", it most likely will be the spy.\n6. When the spy is found, he will say "... how you know that?"\n7. If you try to capture any Qiqirn other then the spy, you will no longer be able to get information from that Qiqirn and you will lose some Assault Points.\n8. The Puk deaggro very quickly, and respawn quick too.\nNote: If you are just looking to complete this mission quickly then select capture on every Qiqirn Spy until you win.\nThe Rune of Release appears within the southwest portion of (I-8).  AP Reward is 1200 base, minus 66 AP per false accusation made.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Price Is Right'] = {
        id = 40,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Periqia',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Assassinate King Goldemar',
        reward = nil,
