        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Defeat Orochi.\n   - A setup of Melee utilizing the Ninja support job combined with a Bard & Red Mage can successfully do this Assault.',
        notes = '1. Orochi is a weaker version of Hydra. It has less HP and regen, although it hits are still potent. It lacks TP regen, making it possible to hold it. It still can lose and regrow heads like a traditional  Hydra family monster.\n2. Uses draw in. The draw in point is range of Serpentine Tail.\n3. Easier to enfeeble than regular Hydra, Elegy and Slow both land without difficulty.\n4. Occasionally during the fight the emote message "Orochi has begun to thrash its tail about" will appear, for about 30-45 seconds Orochi will continually flip towards you so as to face its target with its tail. This allows it to use its flail move, Serpentine Tail. This ends with the emote message "The thrashing has ceased."\n5. Uses all standard Hydra TP attacks.\n   - Serpentine Tail has the ability to one-shot the target of the attack.\n   - Serpentine Tail can be outrun if players run away from Orochi upon the tail begining to thrash.',
    },
